![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/88ddebfe-e36a-44c7-96ef-3d104f6334c5/e376.jpg)

In this episode of the Major Issues Podcast, we’re diving into Justice League: Crisis on Two Earths—the first animated comic book film to tackle the multiverse! We’ll discuss the film’s story, the alternate versions of our favorite heroes, and how it helped pave the way for future multiverse stories in both animation and live-action. Plus, we’re giving props to the legendary Dwayne McDuffie for his unforgettable contribution. Does this 15-year-old classic still hold up? Tune in to find out!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

